    <p>Will you be able to help iden­tify the plant? A few of them ap­peared in my pots. Is it a weed?</p>
    <p>Rob Cheong</p>
    <p>The plant is com­monly called the Livid Amaranth. Its botan­i­cal name is Amaran­thus bli­tum ssp. ol­er­aceus. It oc­curs as a weed where it will grow and self-sow in sur­round­ing ar­eas. The young shoots and leaves can be eaten.</p>

